          <p>Choose photos with natural dark zones (sky, shadows, surfaces) for text placement</p>
          <p>Use white text on dark photo areas, navy text on light photo areas</p>
          <p>Keep text short when overlaying photos — taglines only, not paragraphs</p>
          <p>Test readability at the actual size it will appear (mobile, feed, story)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-rule bg-rule-dont">
          <div class="bg-rule-label">✗ DON'T</div>
          <p>Add drop shadows to text</p>
          <p>Add dark overlays or gradient scrims to photos</p>
          <p>Place text over busy/detailed areas of the photo</p>
          <p>Use thin font weights on photos — always bold/black for overlay text</p>
          <p>Put long copy on photos — move it to a solid-color panel instead</p>
        </div>
